claim.claim-text:
1. An input impedance matching circuit for a low noise amplifier, comprising:
a gate pad configured to receive an input signal;
an input transistor configured to amplify the input signal transmitted from the gate pad;
a source degeneration inductor, electrically coupled to an external ground voltage, for matching input impedance of the low noise amplifier;
a source pad coupled to a source electrode of the input transistor; and
a matching capacitor formed between the gate pad and the source pad by extending the source pad to be disposed under the gate pad.

11. A low noise amplifier comprising:
a gate pad configured to receive an input signal;
an input transistor configured to amplify the input signal transmitted from the gate pad;
a load coupled to a drain electrode of the input transistor;
a source degeneration inductor coupled to an external power supply voltage, adapted for input impedance matching of the low noise amplifier;
a source pad coupled to a source electrode of the input transistor; and
a matching capacitor formed between the gate pad and the source pad by extending the source pad to be disposed under the gate pad.
